photo.description: The angel on top of the Queen Victoria Memorial outside Buckingham Palace in London. Unfortunately it was quite late in the day so the colour only looked good from the back, my photos of the front are quite dull due to the awkward position of the sun :( Some history: The statue was sculpted by Sir Thomas Brock and the surround was constructed by the architect Sir Aston Webb (using 2,300 tons of marble, it is pretty huge). It was dedicated to Queen Victoria by George V and his first cousin, Wilhelm II of Germany, in 1911. It was fully completed in 1914.
